Data analysis

Text

fse

We fitted a linear mixed model (estimated using REML and nloptwrap optimizer) to predict fse with group and time_point (formula: fse ~ 1 + group + time_point + group * time_point). The model included login_id as random effect (formula: ~1 | login_id). The models total explanatory power is substantial (conditional R2 = 0.62) and the part related to the fixed effects alone (marginal R2) is of 0.04. The models intercept, corresponding to group = control and time_point = 1st , is at 17.84 (S.E. = 0.51, p < .001, 95% CI [16.85, 18.84]). Within this model:

  • The effect of group [treatment] is statistically non-significant and positive (beta = 0.08, S.E. = 0.71, p = 0.912, 95% CI [-1.32, 1.48]; Std. beta = 0.02, 95% CI [-0.33, 0.37])
  • The effect of time point [2nd] is statistically non-significant and negative (beta = -0.46, S.E. = 0.49, p = 0.342, 95% CI [-1.41, 0.49]; Std. beta = -0.12, 95% CI [-0.35, 0.12])
  • The interaction effect of time point [2nd] on group [treatment] is statistically significant and positive (beta = 2.19, S.E. = 0.70, p = 0.002, 95% CI [0.82, 3.56]; Std. beta = 0.55, 95% CI [0.20, 0.89])

Standardized parameters were obtained by fitting the model on a standardized version of the dataset. 95% Confidence Intervals (CIs) and p-values were computed using a Wald normal distribution approximation.
